title: Pixie 1.0 - PXE LAN Boot System VirtualBox VM
description:
Pixie 1.0 - PXE LAN Boot System
=========


Loaded with:

Intel Processory Identitifcation Utility
Memtest86+ v4.20
DOS Network Boot Disk v3.55
Parted Magic 2012_11_30
Arch Linux
Windows XP SP3 Unattended Setup
Windows XP SP3 Unattended Setup with DriverPacks
Windows XP SP3 Unattended Setup for Internet Cafe v1.0.7


Instructions:

Attach the VM to the network you want PXE capability on.
The proxyDHCP configuration in Serva32 is compatible with some DHCP servers.
You may be required to disable your router's DHCP and configure Serva32 as a Full DHCP server.
PXE files are located C:PXE
Customise the menu script at C:PXEtftpbootpxelinux.cfgdefault
